# URL & API Monitoring

A Python-based monitoring tool that checks the availability, response time, and HTTP status codes of URLs and APIs, generating logs for analysis and troubleshooting.

## Features

* Monitor URLs and APIs
* Collect HTTP status codes
* Measure response times
* Check service availability (UP/DOWN)
* Generate execution logs
* Record monitoring timestamps

## Technologies

* Python 3.x
* Requests
* Datetime

## Project Structure

```text
project/
│
├── main.py
│
├── monitor/
│   ├── monitoring.py
│   └── logger.py
│
├── logs/
│
└── requirements.txt
```

## Installation

Clone the repository:

```bash
git clone <repository_url>
cd <repository_name>
```

Install dependencies:

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

## Usage

Run the monitoring script:

```bash
python main.py
```

Example output:

```text
URL: https://www.google.com Code: 200 Time: 0.18 seconds. Availability: UP 2026-06-13 23:25:10

URL: https://www.github.com Code: 200 Time: 0.42 seconds. Availability: UP 2026-06-13 23:25:11
```

## Log Generation

The application generates log files containing monitoring results.

Example:

```text
logs/monitoring_20260613.log
```

## Future Improvements

* Export metrics to Prometheus
* Dashboard integration with Grafana
* SSL certificate monitoring
* Email alerts
* Slack/Discord notifications
* Parallel URL checks
* Configuration file support (YAML/JSON)

